      "timestep_posted": 33
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. Power is delivered through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, providing short, tactile throws. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal (RMS). The chassis remains taut, utilizing its original MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension configuration with no signs of hydraulic leakage or significant bushing fatigue. The factory four-piston monobloc calipers provide excellent bite and heat dissipation. While displaying minor patina on the exterior consistent with use, the mechanical integrity and linear power delivery make this an exceptional driver-focused example.",
